  "question": "If $\\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\\\ a & -b & c \\\\ a & b & -c \\end{vmatrix}=kabc$, then the value of $k$ is",
  "options": [
    "(a) 0",
    "(b) 1",
    "(c) 2",
    "(d) 4"
  ],
  "solutionSteps": [
    "Let $\\Delta=\\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\\\ a & -b & c \\\\ a & b & -c \\end{vmatrix}$.",
    "Apply $R_2 \\to R_2-R_1$ and $R_3 \\to R_3-R_1$.",
    "Then $\\Delta=\\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\\\ 0 & -2b & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 & -2c \\end{vmatrix}$.",
    "Expanding along first column:",
    "$\\Delta=a\\begin{vmatrix}-2b & 0 \\\\ 0 & -2c\\end{vmatrix}$.",
    "$=a(4bc)=4abc$.",
    "Hence $k=4$."
  ],
  "finalAnswer": "4",
  "graphRef": ""
}
{
