  "year": "2023",
  "tags": ["Determinants", "Properties", "Equality"],
  "question": "For which value of $x$, are the determinants $\\begin{vmatrix} 2x & -3 \\\\ 5 & x \\end{vmatrix}$ and $\\begin{vmatrix} 10 & 1 \\\\ -3 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}$ equal?",
  "options": [
    "(a) ±3",
    "(b) -3",
    "(c) ±2",
    "(d) 2"
  ],
  "solutionSteps": [
    "First determinant: $D_1=2x(x)-5(-3)=2x^2+15$.",
    "Second determinant: $D_2=10(2)-1(-3)=20+3=23$.",
    "Given $D_1=D_2$.",
    "So $2x^2+15=23$.",
    "$2x^2=8$.",
    "$x^2=4$.",
    "$x=±2$."
  ],
  "finalAnswer": "±2",
  "graphRef": ""
}
