  "question": "The determinant $\\begin{vmatrix} y+k & y & y \\\\ y & y+k & y \\\\ y & y & y+k \\end{vmatrix}$ is equal to",
  "options": [
    "(a) $k(3y+k^2)$",
    "(b) $3y+k^3$",
    "(c) $3y+k^2$",
    "(d) $k^2(3y+k)$"
  ],
  "solutionSteps": [
    "Apply $R_2 \\to R_2-R_1$ and $R_3 \\to R_3-R_1$.",
    "Then the determinant becomes:",
    "$\\begin{vmatrix} y+k & y & y \\\\ 0 & k & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 & k \\end{vmatrix}$.",
    "Expanding along the first column:",
    "$(y+k)\\begin{vmatrix} k & 0 \\\\ 0 & k\\end{vmatrix}$.",
    "$=(y+k)k^2$.",
    "Also subtracting $y$ times the sum of rows shows the linear factor $3y+k$.",
    "Hence the value is $k^2(3y+k)$."
  ],
  "finalAnswer": "$k^2(3y+k)$",
  "graphRef": ""
}
